main event: Two unidentified white, satellite-like objects were seen traveling in the sky over South Wardsboro, Vermont on August 16, 1965.
interesting points: The objects were circular in shape and traveled from southeast to northwest for about 20 seconds.
A jet noise was heard, but the objects were not seen.
A shooting star was observed traveling from east to west after the objects were no longer visible.
There is a handwritten note about the time being 3 minutes fast as checked by a stopwatch.
